{"award_age":66.0,"bio_image":"full\/ab3b352060f99e33d9c4bb7c96184db8194847ae.jpg","category":"Physics","country":"United States","date_of_birth":"1922-07-15T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/1\/1b\/Leon_M._Lederman.jpg\/220px-Leon_M._Lederman.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Leon_M._Lederman","mini_bio":"<p><b>Leon Max Lederman<\/b> (born July 15, 1922) is an American experimental physicist who received, along with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Martin_Lewis_Perl\" title=\"Martin Lewis Perl\">Martin Lewis Perl<\/a>, the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wolf_Prize_in_Physics\" title=\"Wolf Prize in Physics\">Wolf Prize in Physics<\/a> in 1982, for their research on <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Quark\" title=\"Quark\">quarks<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Lepton\" title=\"Lepton\">leptons<\/a>, and the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_for_Physics\" title=\"Nobel Prize for Physics\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Nobel Prize for Physics<\/a> in 1988, along with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Melvin_Schwartz\" title=\"Melvin Schwartz\">Melvin Schwartz<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Jack_Steinberger\" title=\"Jack Steinberger\">Jack Steinberger<\/a>, for their research on <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Neutrino\" title=\"Neutrino\">neutrinos<\/a>. He is Director Emeritus of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fermi_National_Accelerator_Laboratory\" title=\"Fermi National Accelerator Laboratory\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Fermi National Accelerator Laboratory<\/a> (Fermilab) in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Batavia,_Illinois\" title=\"Batavia, Illinois\">Batavia, Illinois<\/a>, USA. He founded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Illinois_Mathematics_and_Science_Academy\" title=\"Illinois Mathematics and Science Academy\">Illinois Mathematics and Science Academy<\/a>, in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Aurora,_Illinois\" title=\"Aurora, Illinois\">Aurora, Illinois<\/a> in 1986, and has served in the capacity of Resident Scholar since 1998.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Nobel_biography_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Leon_M._Lederman#cite_note-Nobel_biography-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> In 2012, he was awarded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Vannevar_Bush_Award\" title=\"Vannevar Bush Award\">Vannevar Bush Award<\/a> for his extraordinary contributions to understanding the basic forces and particles of nature.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Leon_M._Lederman#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Leon M. Lederman","place_of_birth":"New York","place_of_death":null,"text":"Leon M. Lederman , Physics, 1988","year":1988.0}